The paper deals with compressed sensing and sparse recovery, which are topics that fall under the information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of subspace methods and the analysis of performance guarantees suggest that numerical analysis (cs.NA) and systems and control (cs.SI) may also be relevant sub-categories.
